about.description:
The imod Python package is an addition to iMOD and iMODFLOW, intended to facilitate
working with groundwater models from Python. It does this by supporting reading and
writing of the different iMOD file formats to existing objects often used in Python
data processing.

name: imod
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "imod" %}
{% set version = "0.8.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 42c79e89288c35e57842277ff6617ff7bff28cf15401e4e99d466f67cabd2bc5

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - rasterio >=1.0
    - numpy
    - numba
    - scipy
    - xarray >=0.11
    - cftime >=1.0
    - pandas
    - dask
    - affine
    - jinja2
    - cytoolz
    - toolz
    - geopandas
    - scikit-image
    - matplotlib

test:
  imports:
    - imod

about:
  home: https://gitlab.com/deltares/imod/imod-python
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Work with iMOD MODFLOW models'

  description: |
    The imod Python package is an addition to iMOD and iMODFLOW, intended to facilitate
    working with groundwater models from Python. It does this by supporting reading and
    writing of the different iMOD file formats to existing objects often used in Python
    data processing.
  doc_url: https://imod.xyz/
  dev_url: https://gitlab.com/deltares/imod/imod-python

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - visr
    - Huite
